# Company notes

The unofficial pad. Half-formed thoughts, internal discussions worth
remembering, potential directions, things we're chewing on but haven't
committed to.

This file is **instance property** — owned by the company, never
overwritten by `/sync`. Append-mostly; archive old entries when they
stop being useful.

> **What goes here.** Anything that informs strategic thinking but
> isn't formal yet — early product ideas, market observations,
> internal cultural notes, lessons learned, things to revisit later.
>
> **What doesn't.** Architectural decisions (those go in
> [`decisions/`](decisions/)). Risks (those go in
> [`risks/`](risks/)). Incidents (those go in
> [`incidents/`](incidents/)). Active open questions (those go in
> [`open-questions.md`](open-questions.md)). Official company facts
> (those go in [`company-profile.md`](company-profile.md)).

## Format

Each entry: a date heading, freeform content underneath. Newest at
the top. Subject line optional but useful for skim-reading later.

```
## 2026-05-08 — <optional subject>

Whatever you're thinking. As long as you want.

## 2026-05-01 — earlier topic

Earlier note.
```

When something here graduates to a decision, risk, or active
roadmap item, move it to the right artifact and remove it here (or
leave a stub line saying "→ moved to <where>"). Keeps the pad from
becoming a graveyard of stale ideas.

